{"title_page": "The Way You Love Me (Faith Hill song)", "text_new": "{{short description|2000 single by Faith Hill}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = The Way You Love Me\n| cover      = Thewayyouloveme.jpg\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Faith Hill]]\n| album      = [[Breathe (Faith Hill album)|Breathe]]\n| B-side     = Never Gonna Be Your Lady\n| released   = February 29, 2000\n| format     = CD single\n| recorded   =\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = {{hlist|[[Country pop]]|[[dance-pop]]|[[adult contemporary]]}}\n| length     = 3:07 <small>(album version)</small><br>3:32 <small>(radio remix)</small>\n| label      = [[Warner Bros. Records|Warner Bros. Nashville]]\n| writer     = {{hlist|[[Keith Folles\u00e9]]|Michael Dulaney}}\n| producer   = {{hlist|[[Byron Gallimore]]|Faith Hill}}\n| prev_title = [[Breathe (Faith Hill song)|Breathe]]\n| prev_year  = 1999\n| next_title = [[Let's Make Love (song)|Let's Make Love]]\n| next_year  = 2000\n| misc       = {{External music video|type=single|{{YouTube|o8EamHKpdrM|\"The Way You Love Me\"}}}}\n}}\n\n\"'''The Way You Love Me'''\" is a song written by [[Keith Folles\u00e9]] and Michael Dulaney and recorded by American [[country music]] artist [[Faith Hill]]. It was released in February 2000 as the second single from her album ''[[Breathe (Faith Hill album)|Breathe]]''. This song spent four weeks at number one on the ''Billboard'' Country charts in May 2000 and peaked at number six on the ''Billboard'' Hot 100 on December 30, 2000. Worldwide, the song reached number four in Hungary, number nine in Spain and number 15 in the United Kingdom.\n\n==Composition==\n\"The Way You Love Me\" moves at a [[tempo]] of 102 beats per minute.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://songbpm.com/faith-hill/the-way-you|title=BPM for 'the way you' by faith hill {{!}} songbpm.com|website=songbpm.com|access-date=October 9, 2016}}</ref>  The song is set in the key of [[C major]] but is transposed to [[D major]] for the [[Bridge (music)|bridge]] and to [[E major]] in the [[Refrain|chorus]].  The song moves in [[Time signature|common time]], and Hill's vocals span from G<sub>3</sub> to B<sub>4</sub> in the song.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.musicnotes.com/sheetmusic/mtd.asp?ppn=MN0060999|title=Faith Hill \"The Way You Love Me\" Sheet Music in C Major - Download & Print|last=Dulaney|first=Michael|date=|website=Musicnotes.com|publisher=|access-date=October 9, 2016}}</ref>  In the pop version of the song, Hill's backing vocals are [[Auto-Tune]]d.\n\n==Music video==\nThe music video for \"The Way You Love Me\" was directed by [[Joseph Kahn]].<ref>[http://www.ifilm.com/video/2788226 The Way You Love Me - Faith Hill - Music Videos - SPIKE Powered By IFILM<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> It first aired on television the week of August 21, 2000. The music video shows Faith as many different characters, including a mom, police officer, robber, waitress, heiress, and nurse.\n\nThere was also a remix video using the [[Love to Infinity]] remix. The only difference is that Faith is shown as one extra character\u2014a meteorologist. [[Jennette McCurdy]], best known as [[Sam Puckett (iCarly)|Sam Puckett]] on ''[[iCarly]]'', was featured in this video as Hill's daughter in the backseat of a station wagon.{{citation needed|date=May 2018}}\n\n==Track listings==\n\n'''US CD single'''\n#The Way You Love Me (Radio Remix]) \u2013 3:32\n#Never Gonna Be Your Lady \u2013 5:31\n\n'''US maxi-CD'''\n#The Way You Love Me (Love to Infinity Radio Mix) \u2013 3:00  \n#The Way You Love Me (Radio Remix] 3:31\n#The Way You Love Me (Love to Infinity Master Mix) \u2013 6:30\n\n'''US vinyl, 12\", promo'''\n#The Way You Love Me (Love to Infinity Master Mix) \u2013 6:30 \n#The Way You Love Me (Love to Infinity Radio Mix) \u2013 3:00  \n#The Way You Love Me (Radio Remix) \u2013 3:31\n#The Way You Love Me (Love to Infinity Instrumental) \u2013 6:31\n\n'''Europe maxi-CD'''\n#The Way You Love Me (Love to Infinity Radio Mix) \